A leader of the Revolution Now in Osun State, Olawale Bakare and others has been arrested on Wednesday by operatives of the Department of Secret Service (DSS) during a peaceful protest in Osogbo. Bakare and other members of the movement numbering about six were arrested on Wednesday morning while they were addressing journalists at a popular junction, Ola-Iya. The protesters who were armed with placards with several inscriptions against bad governance, lack of infrastructure, extrajudicial activities and others were arrested in the presence of policemen. Other members who were on the scene ran away to avoid arrest. Details shortlyâ€¦